## Production Considerations

| Topic | Homelab | Production |
|---|---|---|
| ACME server | Use production (`acme-v02`) | Use staging first to avoid rate limits during testing |
| Secret management | Plain `issuer-secrets.yaml` in `.gitignore` | Use Sealed Secrets, Vault, or External Secrets Operator |
| Certificate scope | One `ClusterIssuer` for all domains | Consider separate issuers per environment or zone |
| Monitoring | Check certificate status manually | Alert on `Certificate` resources approaching expiry |

### Let's Encrypt Staging Server

When testing your setup for the first time, use the Let's Encrypt staging server to avoid hitting production rate limits. Replace the `server` field in your `ClusterIssuer`:

```yaml
server: https://acme-staging-v02.api.letsencrypt.org/directory
```

Staging certificates are not trusted by browsers but are otherwise functionally identical. Once everything is working, switch to the production server and delete and recreate any staging certificates.